Preamble

The SPEAR Public License exists to protect openness, fairness,
and developer freedom while preventing closed-source exploitation.

You are free to use this Software, even commercially.
But anything built on SPEAR must remain open to everyone.

If you build on SPEAR, you stand with SPEAR.

----------------------------------------------------------------

1. Definitions

"Software" means this project and all source code, binaries,
assets, libraries, documentation, and related materials.

"Derivative Work" means any modified, extended, integrated,
compiled, distributed, or reused form of the Software.

"Public Source" means complete corresponding source code,
including build scripts and dependencies, sufficient to rebuild.

"Commercial Use" includes selling, licensing, SaaS, hosting,
subscriptions, paid services, advertisements, client work,
or any revenue-generating activity.

"Network Use" means providing the Software through servers,
bots, APIs, or any online service accessible by users.

